---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Principles | ForgeCore" description="The principles that govern ForgeCore: determinism, architecture, discipline, compounding, proof, and sequential mastery.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="reading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Principles</p>
      <h1>Doctrine before motion.</h1>
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>Determinism over hype</h3>
        <p>ForgeCore should operate from explicit loops, measurable outcomes, and repeatable decision logic.</p>
        <h3>Architecture over models</h3>
        <p>Models can be swapped. The system should still work because the control layer is durable.</p>
        <h3>Discipline over excitement</h3>
        <p>No strategy sprawl. No publishing for its own sake. No expansion without evidence.</p>
        <h3>Compounding over flash</h3>
        <p>Small structural improvements are worth more than noisy bursts of output.</p>
        <h3>Proof over claims</h3>
        <p>Artifacts, metrics, and public changelogs matter more than ambitious language.</p>
        <h3>Sequential mastery over sprawl</h3>
        <p>Each module should be understood, measured, and hardened before new ones dilute attention.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
